	   <tr><td colspan=2>It has been sometime since I have last posted here and I have always received the guidance I was hoping for when I did from such players as Praetor and a few others. I am now very close to lvl 60, within 15hrs xp time and I find myself at a loss to even go on, my guild rarely recognizes Pallies as anything other than a body to fill a whole as they feel we are not one of the essential classes to survive and excel within the high lvl game. I try to my wits end to contribute/participate in all guild events yet it does not seem as though those are actions are recognized by the guild leadership at all.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am wondering is it really worth it? Is the high end game worth compromising your ideals and pride so as to participate in such events? Is it worth to pump out a lvl 60 paly-usually sitting lfg 3-6hrs per session online when no one even cares if you are partcipating or not and the only time they ask you specifically hey are you coming? is when they don't have enough bodies. Just seems to me my time could be better spent on something else.<br>Is this a problem with Paladins? Hybrids? All classes other than war,cleric,chanter,wizzie? Or is this a problem within my own guild?<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
