	   <tr><td colspan=2>While I am not 60th level (or anywhere close, being only 31st), I can clearly state that I believe this to be a problem with your guild.<br><br>I belong to the Shadows of Honor on Rodcet Nife.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am moving (through a guild merger to Order of the Dragon).  We have one Paladin who is 56th level, and is constantly in demand.  I have no problem finding a group within my guild.  In fact, guild honor codes ask guildies to group with other guildies.  PERIOD!<br><br>Being that Praetor is on the same server as I am, I can state that he is CONSTANTLY busy.  I see him camped in the highest level zones, and I can but assume from his statements to me that he is constantly busy.  I'm sure he'll offer more detail, but I can assure you that his name is one of honor amongst younger Paladins on the server.<br><br>I can also state that I roleplay my character a great deal.  Because of this, people know that I will step in to the way of a blow to save a caster or cleric.  People trust me to do exchanges, merely because I am a Paladin.  Other Paladins give things to me in trust to be used.  And I pass down to other Paladins, the things I can no longer use.  All of this, has generated, at least on Rodcet Nife and within my ring of acquaintances, a strong feeling of goodwill towards Paladins.  Perhaps this would be something you can try on your server.  Don't know.<br><br>Finally, Paladins struggle through adversity.  Perhaps the zones you are trying are not appropriate, right now.  Travel the world.  Spread goodness.  Share with younger Paladins your knowledge and expertise.  Those good works will come back to you in measure beyond your belief.  THAT I TRUST!<br><br>Jainai Sunshadow<br>31st level Paladin of Rodcet Nife on Rodcet Nife<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
